Maintainer: Priyanjali Bukke <postlink.group@gmail.com>
Imports: stats, survival, rstan, nleqslv, label.switching
Description: Provides dedicated statistical tools for post-linkage data analysis (PLDA) to account for record linkage errors, particularly in secondary analyses where linkage and downstream modeling are conducted separately. The package implements a cohesive, formula-based regression modeling interface that adjusts for falsely linked records without requiring direct access to the primary, unlinked files. It consolidates multiple adjustment methodologies into a unified framework, including bias-adjusted estimating equations for generalized linear models (linear, logistic, Poisson, and Gamma) and Cox proportional hazards models. Furthermore, it incorporates a mixture model approach also supporting contingency table analyses, alongside Bayesian mixture approaches that enable parameter estimation and multiple imputation of latent match status.
